SIMPLE: howel
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Howel
<hw>How"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A tool used by coopers
for smoothing and chamfering their work, especially the inside of
casks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Howel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Howel
<hw>How"el</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To smooth; to plane; <as>as, to
<ex>howel</ex> a cask</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Howell</ent>⟦br⟧
